The claim with the title 'How much does La Crosse County have to spend on roads? ' says In an oct. 13 debate between the two candidates running for the 94th District Assembly seat airing on Wisconsin Public Radio, now re-elected Democratic rep. Steve Doyle claimed that the amount of money he receives in state funding to help improve roads and transportation in La Crosse County is significantly less than what he needs. Representative Steve Doyle “ we’ve done studies at the La Crosse County level and we’ve identified $61 million dollars of need that we have, roads that need serious repair and maintenance right now, $61 million, but we’re only able to spend $2.4 million dollars, ” said Doyle on WPR. 
